#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:3
msgid "Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient"
msgstr "深度確定性策略梯度 (Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient)"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:5
msgid "Table of Contents"
msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:8
msgid "Background"
msgstr "背景"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:10
msgid ""
"(Previously: `Introduction to RL Part 1: The Optimal Q-Function and the "
"Optimal Action`_)"
msgstr ""
"（先前章節：`Introduction to RL Part 1: The Optimal Q-Function and the "
"Optimal Action`_）"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:14
msgid ""
"Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) is an algorithm which "
"concurrently learns a Q-function and a policy. It uses off-policy data "
"and the Bellman equation to learn the Q-function, and uses the Q-function"
" to learn the policy."
msgstr ""
"深度確定性策略梯度 (DDPG) 是一種同時學習 Q 函數 (Q-Function) 和策略的演算法。"
"它使用離策略 (Off-policy) 資料和 Bellman 方程式來學習 Q 函數，並使用 Q 函數來"
"學習策略。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:16
msgid ""
"This approach is closely connected to Q-learning, and is motivated the "
"same way: if you know the optimal action-value function :math:`Q^*(s,a)`,"
" then in any given state, the optimal action :math:`a^*(s)` can be found "
"by solving"
msgstr ""
"這種方法與 Q-learning 密切相關，動機也相同：如果你知道最優動作-價值函數 "
":math:`Q^*(s,a)`，那麼在任何給定狀態下，最優動作 :math:`a^*(s)` 可以透過求解"
"以下問題得到"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:18
msgid "a^*(s) = \\arg \\max_a Q^*(s,a)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:22
msgid ""
"DDPG interleaves learning an approximator to :math:`Q^*(s,a)` with "
"learning an approximator to :math:`a^*(s)`, and it does so in a way which"
" is specifically adapted for environments with continuous action spaces. "
"But what does it mean that DDPG is adapted *specifically* for "
"environments with continuous action spaces? It relates to how we compute "
"the max over actions in :math:`\\max_a Q^*(s,a)`."
msgstr ""
"DDPG 交替學習 :math:`Q^*(s,a)` 的近似器和 :math:`a^*(s)` 的近似器，並且以一"
"種專門適應連續動作空間 (Action Space) 環境的方式進行。但 DDPG *專門*適應連續"
"動作空間環境是什麼意思呢？這與我們如何計算 :math:`\\max_a Q^*(s,a)` 中對動作"
"取最大值有關。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:24
msgid ""
"When there are a finite number of discrete actions, the max poses no "
"problem, because we can just compute the Q-values for each action "
"separately and directly compare them. (This also immediately gives us the"
" action which maximizes the Q-value.) But when the action space is "
"continuous, we can't exhaustively evaluate the space, and solving the "
"optimization problem is highly non-trivial. Using a normal optimization "
"algorithm would make calculating :math:`\\max_a Q^*(s,a)` a painfully "
"expensive subroutine. And since it would need to be run every time the "
"agent wants to take an action in the environment, this is unacceptable."
msgstr ""
"當離散動作數量有限時，取最大值不成問題，因為我們可以分別計算每個動作的 Q 值並"
"直接比較。（這也立即給出了使 Q 值最大化的動作。）但當動作空間是連續的時候，我"
"們無法窮舉地評估整個空間，求解這個最佳化問題非常困難。使用一般的最佳化演算法"
"會使計算 :math:`\\max_a Q^*(s,a)` 成為一個代價極其高昂的子程式。而且由於每次"
"代理程式要在環境中執行動作時都需要執行它，這是不可接受的。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:26
msgid ""
"Because the action space is continuous, the function :math:`Q^*(s,a)` is "
"presumed to be differentiable with respect to the action argument. This "
"allows us to set up an efficient, gradient-based learning rule for a "
"policy :math:`\\mu(s)` which exploits that fact. Then, instead of running"
" an expensive optimization subroutine each time we wish to compute "
":math:`\\max_a Q(s,a)`, we can approximate it with :math:`\\max_a Q(s,a) "
"\\approx Q(s,\\mu(s))`. See the Key Equations section details."
msgstr ""
"因為動作空間是連續的，函數 :math:`Q^*(s,a)` 被假設對動作引數可微分。這使我們"
"能夠為策略 :math:`\\mu(s)` 建立一個高效的、基於梯度的學習規則來利用這一事實。"
"然後，我們不需要每次計算 :math:`\\max_a Q(s,a)` 時都執行昂貴的最佳化子程式，"
"而是可以用 :math:`\\max_a Q(s,a) \\approx Q(s,\\mu(s))` 來近似它。詳見關鍵方"
"程式章節。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:30
msgid "Quick Facts"
msgstr "快速概覽"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:32
msgid "DDPG is an off-policy algorithm."
msgstr "DDPG 是一種離策略 (Off-policy) 演算法。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:33
msgid "DDPG can only be used for environments with continuous action spaces."
msgstr "DDPG 只能用於具有連續動作空間的環境。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:34
msgid ""
"DDPG can be thought of as being deep Q-learning for continuous action "
"spaces."
msgstr "DDPG 可以被視為連續動作空間版本的深度 Q-learning。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:35
msgid "The Spinning Up implementation of DDPG does not support parallelization."
msgstr "Spinning Up 的 DDPG 實作不支援平行化。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:38
msgid "Key Equations"
msgstr "關鍵方程式"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:40
msgid ""
"Here, we'll explain the math behind the two parts of DDPG: learning a Q "
"function, and learning a policy."
msgstr "在此，我們將解釋 DDPG 兩個部分背後的數學：學習 Q 函數和學習策略。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:43
msgid "The Q-Learning Side of DDPG"
msgstr "DDPG 的 Q-Learning 面向"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:45
msgid ""
"First, let's recap the Bellman equation describing the optimal action-"
"value function, :math:`Q^*(s,a)`. It's given by"
msgstr ""
"首先，讓我們回顧描述最優動作-價值函數 :math:`Q^*(s,a)` 的 Bellman 方程式。"
"它定義為"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:47
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Q^*(s,a) = \\underset{s' \\sim P}{{\\mathrm E}}\\left[r(s,a) + \\gamma "
"\\max_{a'} Q^*(s', a')\\right]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:51
msgid ""
"where :math:`s' \\sim P` is shorthand for saying that the next state, "
":math:`s'`, is sampled by the environment from a distribution "
":math:`P(\\cdot| s,a)`."
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`s' \\sim P` 是簡寫，表示下一個狀態 :math:`s'` 是環境從分佈 "
":math:`P(\\cdot| s,a)` 中取樣的。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:53
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"This Bellman equation is the starting point for learning an approximator "
"to :math:`Q^*(s,a)`. Suppose the approximator is a neural network "
":math:`Q_{\\phi}(s,a)`, with parameters :math:`\\phi`, and that we have "
"collected a set :math:`{\\mathcal D}` of transitions :math:`(s,a,r,s',d)`"
" (where :math:`d` indicates whether state :math:`s'` is terminal). We can"
" set up a **mean-squared Bellman error (MSBE)** function, which tells us "
"roughly how closely :math:`Q_{\\phi}` comes to satisfying the Bellman "
"equation:"
msgstr ""
"這個 Bellman 方程式是學習 :math:`Q^*(s,a)` 近似器的起點。假設近似器是一個參數"
"為 :math:`\\phi` 的神經網路 :math:`Q_{\\phi}(s,a)`，且我們已收集了一組轉移 "
":math:`{\\mathcal D}`，包含 :math:`(s,a,r,s',d)`（其中 :math:`d` 表示狀態 "
":math:`s'` 是否為終止狀態）。我們可以建立一個**均方 Bellman 誤差 (MSBE)** 函"
"數，大致告訴我們 :math:`Q_{\\phi}` 多接近滿足 Bellman 方程式："

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:55
msgid ""
"L(\\phi, {\\mathcal D}) = \\underset{(s,a,r,s',d) \\sim {\\mathcal "
"D}}{{\\mathrm E}}\\left[\n"
"    \\Bigg( Q_{\\phi}(s,a) - \\left(r + \\gamma (1 - d) \\max_{a'} "
"Q_{\\phi}(s',a') \\right) \\Bigg)^2\n"
"    \\right]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:61
msgid ""
"Here, in evaluating :math:`(1-d)`, we've used a Python convention of "
"evaluating ``True`` to 1 and ``False`` to zero. Thus, when "
"``d==True``---which is to say, when :math:`s'` is a terminal state---the "
"Q-function should show that the agent gets no additional rewards after "
"the current state. (This choice of notation corresponds to what we later "
"implement in code.)"
msgstr ""
"在這裡，在計算 :math:`(1-d)` 時，我們使用了 Python 的慣例，將 ``True`` 視為 "
"1，``False`` 視為零。因此，當 ``d==True``——也就是說，當 :math:`s'` 是終止狀態"
"時——Q 函數應該顯示代理程式在當前狀態之後不會獲得額外獎勵。（這種符號選擇與我"
"們後續在程式碼中的實作相對應。）"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:63
msgid ""
"Q-learning algorithms for function approximators, such as DQN (and all "
"its variants) and DDPG, are largely based on minimizing this MSBE loss "
"function. There are two main tricks employed by all of them which are "
"worth describing, and then a specific detail for DDPG."
msgstr ""
"用於函數近似器的 Q-learning 演算法，如 DQN（及其所有變體）和 DDPG，主要基於最"
"小化這個 MSBE 損失函數。它們都使用了兩個值得描述的主要技巧，以及一個 DDPG 的"
"特定細節。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:65
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Trick One: Replay Buffers.** All standard algorithms for training a "
"deep neural network to approximate :math:`Q^*(s,a)` make use of an "
"experience replay buffer. This is the set :math:`{\\mathcal D}` of "
"previous experiences. In order for the algorithm to have stable behavior,"
" the replay buffer should be large enough to contain a wide range of "
"experiences, but it may not always be good to keep everything. If you "
"only use the very-most recent data, you will overfit to that and things "
"will break; if you use too much experience, you may slow down your "
"learning. This may take some tuning to get right."
msgstr ""
"**技巧一：經驗回放緩衝區 (Replay Buffer)。** 所有用於訓練深度神經網路以近似 "
":math:`Q^*(s,a)` 的標準演算法都使用經驗回放緩衝區。這就是先前經驗的集合 "
":math:`{\\mathcal D}`。為了使演算法具有穩定的行為，回放緩衝區應該足夠大以包含"
"廣泛的經驗，但保留所有內容並不總是好的。如果你只使用最近的資料，你會過度擬合"
"並導致問題；如果你使用太多經驗，可能會減慢學習速度。這可能需要一些調整才能做"
"好。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:67 ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:123
#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:176
msgid "You Should Know"
msgstr "你應該知道"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:69
msgid ""
"We've mentioned that DDPG is an off-policy algorithm: this is as good a "
"point as any to highlight why and how. Observe that the replay buffer "
"*should* contain old experiences, even though they might have been "
"obtained using an outdated policy. Why are we able to use these at all? "
"The reason is that the Bellman equation *doesn't care* which transition "
"tuples are used, or how the actions were selected, or what happens after "
"a given transition, because the optimal Q-function should satisfy the "
"Bellman equation for *all* possible transitions. So any transitions that "
"we've ever experienced are fair game when trying to fit a Q-function "
"approximator via MSBE minimization."
msgstr ""
"我們已經提到 DDPG 是一種離策略演算法：這裡正好可以重點說明原因和方式。注意回"
"放緩衝區*應該*包含舊的經驗，即使這些經驗可能是用過時的策略獲得的。為什麼我們"
"能使用這些舊經驗呢？原因在於 Bellman 方程式*不在乎*使用的是哪些轉移元組，也"
"不在乎動作是如何選擇的，或者給定轉移之後發生了什麼，因為最優 Q 函數應該對*所"
"有*可能的轉移都滿足 Bellman 方程式。所以我們曾經歷過的任何轉移，在透過 MSBE "
"最小化來擬合 Q 函數近似器時都是可以使用的。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:71
msgid ""
"**Trick Two: Target Networks.** Q-learning algorithms make use of "
"**target networks**. The term"
msgstr ""
"**技巧二：目標網路 (Target Network)。** Q-learning 演算法使用**目標網路**。"
"以下這一項"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:73
#, python-brace-format
msgid "r + \\gamma (1 - d) \\max_{a'} Q_{\\phi}(s',a')"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:77
msgid ""
"is called the **target**, because when we minimize the MSBE loss, we are "
"trying to make the Q-function be more like this target. Problematically, "
"the target depends on the same parameters we are trying to train: "
":math:`\\phi`. This makes MSBE minimization unstable. The solution is to "
"use a set of parameters which comes close to :math:`\\phi`, but with a "
"time delay---that is to say, a second network, called the target network,"
" which lags the first. The parameters of the target network are denoted "
":math:`\\phi_{\\text{targ}}`."
msgstr ""
"被稱為**目標值**，因為當我們最小化 MSBE 損失時，我們試圖讓 Q 函數更接近這個"
"目標值。問題在於，目標值依賴於我們正在訓練的相同參數 :math:`\\phi`。這使得 "
"MSBE 最小化變得不穩定。解決方案是使用一組接近 :math:`\\phi` 但有時間延遲的參"
"數——也就是說，使用第二個網路，稱為目標網路，它滯後於第一個網路。目標網路的參數"
"記為 :math:`\\phi_{\\text{targ}}`。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:79
msgid ""
"In DQN-based algorithms, the target network is just copied over from the "
"main network every some-fixed-number of steps. In DDPG-style algorithms, "
"the target network is updated once per main network update by polyak "
"averaging:"
msgstr ""
"在基於 DQN 的演算法中，目標網路每隔固定步數從主網路直接複製。在 DDPG 風格的"
"演算法中，目標網路在每次主網路更新時透過 Polyak 平均進行一次更新："

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:81
msgid ""
"\\phi_{\\text{targ}} \\leftarrow \\rho \\phi_{\\text{targ}} + (1 - \\rho)"
" \\phi,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:85
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\rho` is a hyperparameter between 0 and 1 (usually close to"
" 1). (This hyperparameter is called ``polyak`` in our code)."
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`\\rho` 是一個介於 0 和 1 之間的超參數（通常接近 1）。（此超參數在"
"我們的程式碼中稱為 ``polyak``）。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:88
msgid ""
"**DDPG Detail: Calculating the Max Over Actions in the Target.** As "
"mentioned earlier: computing the maximum over actions in the target is a "
"challenge in continuous action spaces. DDPG deals with this by using a "
"**target policy network** to compute an action which approximately "
"maximizes :math:`Q_{\\phi_{\\text{targ}}}`. The target policy network is "
"found the same way as the target Q-function: by polyak averaging the "
"policy parameters over the course of training."
msgstr ""
"**DDPG 細節：計算目標值中對動作的最大化。** 如前所述：在連續動作空間中計算目"
"標值中對動作的最大化是一個挑戰。DDPG 透過使用**目標策略網路**來計算一個近似最"
"大化 :math:`Q_{\\phi_{\\text{targ}}}` 的動作來解決此問題。目標策略網路的獲得"
"方式與目標 Q 函數相同：在訓練過程中對策略參數進行 Polyak 平均。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:90
msgid ""
"Putting it all together, Q-learning in DDPG is performed by minimizing "
"the following MSBE loss with stochastic gradient descent:"
msgstr ""
"綜合以上所有內容，DDPG 中的 Q-learning 是透過隨機梯度下降 (Stochastic "
"Gradient Descent) 最小化以下 MSBE 損失來執行的："

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:92
msgid ""
"L(\\phi, {\\mathcal D}) = \\underset{(s,a,r,s',d) \\sim {\\mathcal "
"D}}{{\\mathrm E}}\\left[\n"
"    \\Bigg( Q_{\\phi}(s,a) - \\left(r + \\gamma (1 - d) "
"Q_{\\phi_{\\text{targ}}}(s', \\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}(s')) \\right) "
"\\Bigg)^2\n"
"    \\right],"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:98
msgid "where :math:`\\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}` is the target policy."
msgstr "其中 :math:`\\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}` 是目標策略。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:102
msgid "The Policy Learning Side of DDPG"
msgstr "DDPG 的策略學習面向"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:104
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Policy learning in DDPG is fairly simple. We want to learn a "
"deterministic policy :math:`\\mu_{\\theta}(s)` which gives the action "
"that maximizes :math:`Q_{\\phi}(s,a)`. Because the action space is "
"continuous, and we assume the Q-function is differentiable with respect "
"to action, we can just perform gradient ascent (with respect to policy "
"parameters only) to solve"
msgstr ""
"DDPG 中的策略學習相當簡單。我們想要學習一個確定性策略 (Deterministic Policy) "
":math:`\\mu_{\\theta}(s)`，它給出使 :math:`Q_{\\phi}(s,a)` 最大化的動作。因為"
"動作空間是連續的，且我們假設 Q 函數對動作可微分，我們可以直接執行梯度上升 "
"(Gradient Ascent)（僅對策略參數）來求解"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:106
msgid ""
"\\max_{\\theta} \\underset{s \\sim {\\mathcal D}}{{\\mathrm E}}\\left[ "
"Q_{\\phi}(s, \\mu_{\\theta}(s)) \\right]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:110
msgid "Note that the Q-function parameters are treated as constants here."
msgstr "注意這裡 Q 函數的參數被視為常數。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:115
msgid "Exploration vs. Exploitation"
msgstr "探索與利用"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:117
msgid ""
"DDPG trains a deterministic policy in an off-policy way. Because the "
"policy is deterministic, if the agent were to explore on-policy, in the "
"beginning it would probably not try a wide enough variety of actions to "
"find useful learning signals. To make DDPG policies explore better, we "
"add noise to their actions at training time. The authors of the original "
"DDPG paper recommended time-correlated `OU noise`_, but more recent "
"results suggest that uncorrelated, mean-zero Gaussian noise works "
"perfectly well. Since the latter is simpler, it is preferred. To "
"facilitate getting higher-quality training data, you may reduce the scale"
" of the noise over the course of training. (We do not do this in our "
"implementation, and keep noise scale fixed throughout.)"
msgstr ""
"DDPG 以離策略的方式訓練一個確定性策略。因為策略是確定性的，如果代理程式進行"
"同策略探索 (Exploration)，在初期可能不會嘗試足夠多樣的動作來找到有用的學習信"
"號。為了讓 DDPG 策略更好地探索，我們在訓練時為動作添加雜訊。原始 DDPG 論文的"
"作者推薦時間相關的 `OU noise`_（OU 雜訊），但更近期的結果表明，不相關的零均值"
"高斯雜訊效果也很好。由於後者更簡單，因此更受青睞。為了促進獲得更高品質的訓練"
"資料，你可以在訓練過程中逐步降低雜訊的強度。（我們在實作中不這樣做，在整個訓"
"練過程中保持雜訊強度固定。）"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:119
msgid ""
"At test time, to see how well the policy exploits what it has learned, we"
" do not add noise to the actions."
msgstr "在測試時，為了觀察策略如何利用 (Exploitation) 所學到的知識，我們不對動作添加雜訊。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:125
msgid ""
"Our DDPG implementation uses a trick to improve exploration at the start "
"of training. For a fixed number of steps at the beginning (set with the "
"``start_steps`` keyword argument), the agent takes actions which are "
"sampled from a uniform random distribution over valid actions. After "
"that, it returns to normal DDPG exploration."
msgstr ""
"我們的 DDPG 實作使用了一個技巧來改善訓練初期的探索。在開始的固定步數內（透過"
" ``start_steps`` 關鍵字引數設定），代理程式從有效動作的均勻隨機分佈中取樣動"
"作。之後，它恢復到正常的 DDPG 探索方式。"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:129
msgid "Pseudocode"
msgstr "虛擬碼"

#: ../../algorithms/ddpg.rst:131
msgid ""
"\\begin{algorithm}[H]\n"
"    \\caption{Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient}\n"
"    \\label{alg1}\n"
"\\begin{algorithmic}[1]\n"
"    \\STATE Input: initial policy parameters $\\theta$, Q-function "
"parameters $\\phi$, empty replay buffer $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"    \\STATE Set target parameters equal to main parameters "
"$\\theta_{\\text{targ}} \\leftarrow \\theta$, $\\phi_{\\text{targ}} "
"\\leftarrow \\phi$\n"
"    \\REPEAT\n"
"        \\STATE Observe state $s$ and select action $a = "
"\\text{clip}(\\mu_{\\theta}(s) + \\epsilon, a_{Low}, a_{High})$, where "
"$\\epsilon \\sim \\mathcal{N}$\n"
"        \\STATE Execute $a$ in the environment\n"
"        \\STATE Observe next state $s'$, reward $r$, and done signal $d$ "
"to indicate whether $s'$ is terminal\n"
"        \\STATE Store $(s,a,r,s',d)$ in replay buffer $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"        \\STATE If $s'$ is terminal, reset environment state.\n"
"        \\IF{it's time to update}\n"
"            \\FOR{however many updates}\n"
"                \\STATE Randomly sample a batch of transitions, $B = \\{ "
"(s,a,r,s',d) \\}$ from $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"                \\STATE Compute targets\n"
"                \\begin{equation*}\n"
"                    y(r,s',d) = r + \\gamma (1-d) "
"Q_{\\phi_{\\text{targ}}}(s', \\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}(s'))\n"
"                \\end{equation*}\n"
"                \\STATE Update Q-function by one step of gradient descent"
" using\n"
"                \\begin{equation*}\n"
"                    \\nabla_{\\phi} \\frac{1}{|B|}\\sum_{(s,a,r,s',d) "
"\\in B} \\left( Q_{\\phi}(s,a) - y(r,s',d) \\right)^2\n"
"                \\end{equation*}\n"
"                \\STATE Update policy by one step of gradient ascent "
"using\n"
"                \\begin{equation*}\n"
"                    \\nabla_{\\theta} \\frac{1}{|B|}\\sum_{s \\in "
"B}Q_{\\phi}(s, \\mu_{\\theta}(s))\n"
"                \\end{equation*}\n"
"                \\STATE Update target networks with\n"
"                \\begin{align*}\n"
"                    \\phi_{\\text{targ}} &\\leftarrow \\rho "
"\\phi_{\\text{targ}} + (1-\\rho) \\phi \\\\\n"
"                    \\theta_{\\text{targ}} &\\leftarrow \\rho "
"\\theta_{\\text{targ}} + (1-\\rho) \\theta\n"
"                \\end{align*}\n"
"            \\ENDFOR\n"
"        \\ENDIF\n"
"    \\UNTIL{convergence}\n"
"\\end{algorithmic}\n"
"\\end{algorithm}"
msgstr ""

